Expand $(2x^5 + 3x^2)(x^4 - 4x^2 + 3x - 8)$.
inference:
Expanding $(2x^5 + 3x^2)(x^4 - 4x^2 + 3x - 8)$, we distribute each term in the first polynomial to each term in the second polynomial.

$2x^5(x^4) + 2x^5(-4x^2) + 2x^5(3x) + 2x^5(-8) + 3x^2(x^4) + 3x^2(-4x^2) + 3x^2(3x) + 3x^2(-8)$

$= 2x^9 - 8x^7 + 6x^6 - 16x^5 + 3x^6 - 12x^4 + 9x^3 - 24x^2$

Now combine like terms.

$= 2x^9 - 8x^7 + (6x^6 + 3x^6) - 16x^5 - 12x^4 + 9x^3 - 24x^2$

$= 2x^9 - 8x^7 + 9x^6 - 16x^5 - 12x^4 + 9x^3 - 24x^2$

Final Answer: $\boxed{2x^9 - 8x^7 + 9x^6 - 16x^5 - 12x^4 + 9x^3 - 24x^2}$
